# grapher_multifn_table_smoke.numos — Phase 9E. Two implicit functions ("x" and
# "2x"), then the Table tab. Screenshot, assert. Proves the Phase 9E multi-column
# table header fix: rebuildTable() now emits one centered header label per active
# column ("x", "f1(x)", "f2(x)") aligned to the data columns with a separator
# between each (GrapherApp.cpp), instead of labelling only x+f1 and slicing the
# f1 text with a fixed mid-screen separator. Expected data over the default range
# (start -5, step 1): f1(x)=x, f2(x)=2x  (e.g. x=-5 -> -5, -10).
#
# Warning-only candidate (no golden blessed; the compare step warns when absent).
log "grapher_multifn_table_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200
open_app Grapher
wait 60
key down
key enter
key x
key enter
wait 40
key down
key enter
key 2
key x
key enter
wait 60
key table
wait 160
screenshot out/grapher_multifn_table_smoke.ppm
assert_app Grapher
log "grapher_multifn_table_smoke: x | f1(x) | f2(x) columns rendered"
